whole_object: It seems even the cars are pooling together on this wet day — nobody likes to drive alone in the rain!
single_object:
- Buildings: "These buildings are so close, they've been thinking of starting a brick-and-mortar social network."
- Cars: "Why don't cars ever get tired? Because they come with their own set of wheels!"
- Traffic lights: "A traffic light turned green and saw all the cars go. It thought to itself, 'I knew I had the power to move people.'"
- Crosswalk: "This crosswalk is so popular, it's practically a pedestrian's runway."
- Trash can: "You know the trash can considers itself quite the 'can'-do personality in the world of waste management."
- Street lights: "The street lights are the city's way of giving the stars a run for their money."
- People: "People like to walk in the rain because it’s the only time no one can see them cry, or maybe they just like puddles."
- Trees: "Why did the tree worry about making friends? It couldn't get out of its bark to meet new leaves!"
multi_object:
- Buildings  
- Cars  
- "These buildings are so tall, they must be trying to outshine the cars with their skyscraper personalities!"  

- Cars  
- Traffic lights  
- "The cars are playing a game of red light, green light, but I think the traffic lights are just enjoying the drama!"  

- Traffic lights  
- Crosswalk  
- "The traffic lights are like the referees of the street, making sure the crosswalk doesn’t get too carried away with its pedestrian dance!"  

- Crosswalk  
- Trees  
- "The crosswalk is like a runway for pedestrians, but those trees are the overzealous paparazzi snapping every step!"  

- Trash can  
- Street lights  
- "The trash can is feeling a bit down, but the street lights keep shining bright, reminding it that every can has its day!"  

- Street lights  
- People  
- "The street lights are like the spotlight on a stage, but the people are the real stars, just trying to avoid a wardrobe malfunction in the rain!"  

- People  
- Trees  
- "The people are huddled under their umbrellas, while the trees are just standing there, showing off their natural 'leaf' of absence!"  

- Trees  
- Buildings  
- "The trees are whispering secrets to the buildings, but I think the buildings are just pretending to listen while they tower over them!"
